The Voice of Conscience

Perilous heights
1932
TOI take:
Published on: Aug 11, 2024
This iconic image, capturing workers perched high above the city, humanizes the immense risks faced by those who built America's skyscrapers. The photo immortalizes their bravery and the precariousness of their lives, while also highlighting the anonymity of the countless laborers whose efforts shaped the skyline yet remained unsung.
Eyes of starvation
1967
Don McCullin
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: Aug 06, 2024
This photograph of starving children in Biafra captured the world's attention during the Nigerian Civil War. The stark depiction of suffering and malnutrition not only raised global awareness but also galvanized humanitarian efforts. The image underscored urgency for aid and contributed to establishment of welfare organizations.
Lost childhood
1943
TOI take:
Published on: Jul 30, 2024
The image from World War II, etched in history, captured the fear and innocence of a young boy surrendering to a German soldier. This image epitomizes the profound impact of war on children, stripping away their innocence and subjecting them to unimaginable horrors and trauma.
